  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best books of body language?",
  "response": "Understanding body language is essential for improving communication, interpreting nonverbal cues, and enhancing interpersonal skills. Here are some of the best books on body language that are widely recommended:\n\n1. **\"What Every BODY is Saying\" by Joe Navarro**  \n   - Written by a former FBI agent, this book provides insights into reading nonverbal cues and understanding human behavior. It\u2019s practical and filled with real-life examples.\n\n2. **\"The Definitive Book of Body Language\" by Allan and Barbara Pease**  \n   - This comprehensive guide covers a wide range of body language signals, from facial expressions to gestures. It\u2019s easy to read and often used as a go-to resource.\n\n3. **\"Body Language: How to Read Others' Thoughts by Their Gestures\" by Allan Pease**  \n   - Another classic by Allan Pease, this book focuses on decoding gestures and subtle signals in everyday interactions.\n\n4. **\"Emotions Revealed: Recognizing Faces and Feelings to Improve Communication and Emotional Life\" by Paul Ekman**  \n   - Written by a pioneer in the study of emotions and facial expressions, this book teaches how to recognize and interpret emotions accurately.\n\n5. **\"The Power of Body Language\" by Tonya Reiman**  \n   - This book explores how to use body language to your advantage in personal and professional settings, with actionable advice.\n\n6. **\"Super Body Language\" by Paul McKenna**  \n   - A practical guide to understanding and using body language effectively, written by a well-known hypnotist and self-help author.\n\n7. **\"Body Language for Dummies\" by Elizabeth Kuhnke**  \n   - Part of the \"For Dummies\" series, this book is a beginner-friendly guide to understanding and improving your nonverbal communication skills.\n\n8. **\"The Silent Language of Leaders: How Body Language Can Help\u2014or Hurt\u2014How You Lead\" by Carol Kinsey Goman**  \n   - Focused on leadership, this book explains how body language impacts authority, influence, and communication in professional environments.\n\n9. **\"You Say More Than You Think\" by Janine Driver**  \n   - This book offers a unique perspective on body language, emphasizing how to align your nonverbal communication with your intentions.\n\n10. **\"Micro Expressions: How to Recognize Subtle Emotions\" by David Matsumoto and Hyi Sung Hwang**  \n    - A detailed guide to spotting micro-expressions, which are brief, involuntary facial expressions that reveal true emotions.\n\nThese books provide a mix of theory, practical advice, and real-world examples to help you master the art of interpreting and using body language effectively. Depending on your specific needs, you can choose one or more to deepen your understanding.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
